<task id="010" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>D2-01 Seed `sprk_analysisaction` row "Summarize Document for Chat" (Dataverse data deploy)</title>
    <status>complete</status>
    <estimated-effort>2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort>~1 hour (definition-authoring portion only; combined with task 011 into one JSON file; main session handles the Dataverse deploy + commit)</actual-effort>
    <assigned>AI Agent</assigned>
    <started>2026-06-04</started>
    <completed>2026-06-04</completed>
    <phase>Phase 2 — Vertical Slice + Insights Tool Integration</phase>
    <wave>P2-G1 (parallel-safe with 011; first task of Phase 2)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>Phase 1 ✅</dependencies>
    <tags>dataverse, seed, playbook, data-deploy</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Seed a NEW `sprk_analysisaction` row "Summarize Document for Chat" (action code
    `SUM-CHAT@v1`) into Spaarke Dev Dataverse. The row carries the JPS-formatted
    system prompt + output schema tuned for the R5 chat-driven Summarize vertical
    slice. This action becomes the prompt-bearing primitive that the downstream
    `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` (task 012) + `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{id}/summarize`
    endpoint (task 014) bind to via `sprk_actionid` on the playbook node row that
    task 011 (D2-02) seeds.

    R5 CLAUDE.md §10 gotcha (BINDING): R5 MUST NOT introduce a new prompt-bearing
    Dataverse entity. `sprk_analysisaction.sprk_systemprompt` IS the JPS prompt
    primitive — this lock-in was inherited from Insights r2 explicit decision. New
    playbooks add new ACTION rows; they do NOT add new entities or store prompts in
    `.txt` files. This task seeds exactly one new ACTION row alongside the existing 11
    rows (the 6 Insights actions INS-FACT/IDXR/EVID/GRND/DECL/RART plus 5 legacy
    R-actions).

    Output schema is tuned for the streaming-aware Workspace renderer (D2-07
    `StructuredOutputStreamWidget`) per spec FR-02: top-level fields TL;DR
    (`tldr`), summary (`summary`), per-file highlights (`fileHighlights`),
    mentioned parties (`mentionedParties`), and call-to-action (`callToAction`).
    These field paths are the load-bearing contract for the `FieldDelta` SSE event
    `Path` values that task 006 (D1-06) emits and the Workspace widget consumes.

    R5 is configuration-first. This task is PURE DATA — no BFF code change, no DI
    change, no schema change. BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB by construction.
    Deployment is via `scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1` (the same script Insights r2
    uses to deploy `predict-matter-cost@v1` and `universal-ingest@v1`).

    Idempotency is BINDING: re-running the seed against an environment that already
    has the action row MUST be a no-op (upsert by `sprk_actioncode`). This protects
    against accidental dual-deploys during R5 Phase 2 ramp-up and is consistent with
    `scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1`'s existing skip-on-exists semantics (line 528-572
    `Step 5: Check for existing playbook`); the same pattern MUST apply to the action
    row lookup in this task.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior Dataverse data engineer with deep familiarity with: the
    `sprk_analysisaction` entity contract (`sprk_actioncode` lookup field,
    `sprk_systemprompt` JPS payload, `sprk_actiontype` lookup, `sprk_outputschemajson`
    or equivalent output-schema field per existing Insights ACTIONS), the
    `scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1` deployment harness (idempotent OData v9.2 POST/PATCH
    against `sprk_analysisactions` collection with Azure CLI bearer-token auth), and
    JPS (JSON Prompt Schema) prompt + output-schema authoring conventions per
    `docs/architecture/playbook-architecture.md`.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A new `sprk_analysisaction` row with `sprk_actioncode = "SUM-CHAT@v1"` and
    `sprk_name = "Summarize Document for Chat"` is visible in Spaarke Dev Dataverse,
    carrying: (a) `sprk_systemprompt` = JPS-formatted prompt instructing the LLM to
    produce a streaming-friendly structured summary with the five top-level fields
    matching the D2-07 widget contract; (b) `sprk_actiontypeid` linked to the
    appropriate action-type lookup row (`0 - AiAnalysis` or equivalent — the same
    type used by existing R-action Summarize rows); (c) an output schema (stored in
    whatever field the existing Summarize-pattern action uses — likely
    `sprk_outputschemajson` or embedded in `sprk_configjson`) defining a JSON schema
    over `tldr` / `summary` / `fileHighlights` / `mentionedParties` / `callToAction`
    suitable for Azure OpenAI Structured Outputs mode (per task 006). The deploy is
    idempotent — re-running the seed produces no duplicate rows and no error.
    `code-review` + `adr-check` at Step 9.5 pass. BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB
    (confirmed in task notes — no BFF code touched). The new action row is consumed
    by task 011 (D2-02) as the FK target for the new `sprk_analysisplaybook` row's
    node.
  </goal>

