  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §10 gotcha (BINDING)">MUST NOT add a new prompt-bearing Dataverse entity. `sprk_analysisaction.sprk_systemprompt` IS the JPS prompt primitive (lock-in inherited from Insights r2). MUST NOT store the system prompt in a `.txt` file or any new entity. This task creates exactly ONE new row in the existing `sprk_analysisactions` collection.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 (Reuse mandate)">MUST use `scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1` (the Insights-r2-proven harness already in the repo) for the deploy invocation OR a thin equivalent that reuses its OData/auth helpers. MUST NOT introduce a parallel deploy mechanism (e.g., new pac CLI workflow, new PowerShell file outside `scripts/`, Python script, etc.).</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2 (no new feature flags)">N/A for this task (no BFF code, no DI). Confirm in notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013 (refined 2026-05-20)">N/A for this task (no BFF service touches, no AI-internal injection). Confirm in notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">N/A for this task (no index document writes; `tenantId`/`sessionId` constraint applies to RAG index writes by task 003, not to action-row seeds). Confirm in notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029 + R5 NFR-07">BFF publish-size delta MUST be 0 MB. Confirmed by construction: this task touches zero `.cs` files and zero project files. Report `0 MB` explicitly in task notes per CLAUDE.md §10 per-task verification rule. No `dotnet publish` measurement required (no BFF code changed).</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 spec FR-02">Output schema field paths MUST match the streaming consumer expectation: `tldr` (array of strings), `summary` (string), `fileHighlights` (array of `{ fileId, fileName, highlights[] }`), `mentionedParties` (array of strings), `callToAction` (string). These exact JSON paths are the contract D2-07 `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` consumes via `FieldDelta.Path` values from task 006.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 spec FR-01">Action's `sprk_systemprompt` MUST be JPS-formatted (NOT a free-text prompt). Use the existing Insights INS-* actions as the JPS-format reference. The prompt MUST instruct streaming-aware output (emit `tldr` first, then `summary`, then `fileHighlights`, then `mentionedParties` + `callToAction`) to align with the D1-06 incremental JSON parser's path-emission order.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 spec FR-11">Output schema MUST support the decline-to-find structured response variant. Either (a) the schema defines an optional `decline` discriminated branch with the 5-field DeclineResponse shape (`reason`, `explanation`, `suggested_actions`, `confidence_in_decline`, `metadata`); OR (b) the decline path is delegated entirely to `DeclineToFindNode` per Insights pattern and the schema omits decline fields (typical). Decision MUST be recorded in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 reuse mandate (R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1)">MUST inspect existing Summarize-pattern action rows (and `predict-matter-cost@v1` + `universal-ingest@v1` reference playbooks) before authoring the prompt + output-schema shape. Cite the reference action(s) in task notes. If proposing any structural deviation from the existing pattern, MUST justify with the gap explicitly.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (idempotency — BINDING)">Re-running the seed deploy against an environment that already has the row MUST be a no-op (skip-on-exists) and MUST NOT fail with a uniqueness violation. `Deploy-Playbook.ps1` enforces this for playbooks via name-lookup at Step 5; the action-row seed MUST mirror the pattern via `sprk_actioncode = 'SUM-CHAT@v1'` lookup before insert. Use `-Force` semantics only when an explicit recreate is desired.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (no BFF or DI change)">This task is PURE DATA. Zero modifications to `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` or any `.cs` file. Zero modifications to any DI module. Zero modifications to `Program.cs`. If the implementation surfaces a need to touch any of these, STOP and escalate per R5 CLAUDE.md §6 — likely a scope mismatch with task 010's plan.md placement.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010 (DI minimalism)">N/A for this task (no DI registrations). Confirm in notes.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>dataverse/jps-action-seed</topic>
