    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Action-row lookup-then-insert idempotency" location="scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1 (Step 5, lines 514-572)">
        `Deploy-Playbook.ps1` checks for existing playbook by `sprk_name` BEFORE insert
        (lines 521-525); when found WITHOUT `-Force`, exits cleanly with the "already
        exists" message and exit code 0. For the action-row seed, mirror this pattern
        against `sprk_analysisactions` filtered by `sprk_actioncode` (per the existing
        Insights INS-* deploy convention surfaced in lines 395-405 `Resolve-ScopeCode`).
        Implementation choice: either (a) author a sibling script
        `scripts/Deploy-AnalysisAction.ps1` reusing the same `Get-DataverseHeaders` /
        `Invoke-DataversePost` helpers, OR (b) extend `Deploy-Playbook.ps1` itself to
        seed referenced actions when not yet present (preferred per R5 §3.1 reuse
        mandate — keeps the harness consolidated). Decision recorded in task notes.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="JPS system-prompt structure" location="docs/architecture/playbook-architecture.md + existing Insights actions">
        The `sprk_systemprompt` field on `sprk_analysisaction` carries the JPS-formatted
        prompt. Existing Insights actions (INS-FACT / INS-IDXR / INS-EVID / INS-GRND /
        INS-DECL / INS-RART) are the binding reference shape. For SUM-CHAT@v1, the
        prompt instructs the LLM to:
        1. Read the supplied document chunks (passed via the orchestrator runtime context).
        2. Emit a structured response matching the output schema (5 top-level fields).
        3. Emit `tldr` FIRST (3-5 bullet strings; ≤140 chars each), then `summary`
           prose (≤2 paragraphs), then per-file highlights, then parties + CTA.
        4. Decline with `DeclineToFindNode` semantics if content is insufficient per
           D-04 honesty contract (per spec FR-11).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Output schema JSON-Schema shape" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/Playbooks/predict-matter-cost.playbook.json + Layer 2 outcome-extraction.v1.schema.json (Insights)">
        Output schema is JSON Schema draft-07. Stored on the action row in
        `sprk_outputschemajson` (string-typed) OR embedded in `sprk_configjson`
        depending on existing convention — VERIFY at Step 2 by reading an existing
        Summarize-pattern action row from Spaarke Dev. Schema MUST be Azure OpenAI
        Structured Outputs compatible (no unsupported keywords; `additionalProperties:
        false` on objects; required arrays populated). Field paths drive the
        `FieldDelta.Path` emissions from task 006.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Scope code naming convention" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/Routing/InsightsActionRouter.cs + predict-matter-cost.playbook.json">
        Action codes follow `<SCOPE>-<MNEMONIC>@<VERSION>`. Insights uses `INS-*@v1`.
        For R5 Summarize-for-Chat, propose `SUM-CHAT@v1` (consistent with `@v1` versioning
        + 3-letter scope prefix `SUM` matching Summarize semantic). VERIFY no existing
        code conflicts at Step 2 by querying Dataverse for `sprk_actioncode eq 'SUM-CHAT@v1'`
        before deploying.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      The R5 chat-driven Summarize vertical slice (spec FR-01 through FR-08) ships a
      new direct endpoint (`POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{id}/summarize`, task 014) and
      a parallel agent-tool function (`InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool`, task 015), both
      delegating to a shared internal `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` (task 012). The
      orchestrator drives a JPS playbook whose first (and primary) node is an LLM
      analysis node bound to the `Summarize Document for Chat` action row. The action
      row's `sprk_systemprompt` IS the prompt; the action row's output-schema field IS
      the structured-outputs JSON schema that Azure OpenAI's Structured Outputs mode
      (task 006) enforces; the action row's `sprk_actiontype` lookup IS the dispatch
      key the playbook executor uses to select the right `INodeExecutor`.

      This task (010) and task 011 (D2-02 playbook config) together unblock the entire
      Phase 2 Summarize implementation path. The action row is referenced by `actionCode`
      in the playbook JSON deployed by task 011; without this seed, task 011's
      `Deploy-Playbook.ps1` invocation would fail at lines 446-510 (Pre-Flight Failed —
      `Action 'SUM-CHAT@v1' not found`).

      The action-row primitive is the BINDING lock-in from Insights r2 (per R5 CLAUDE.md
      §10): NO new prompt-bearing entity. Every R5 playbook (Summarize for Chat now;
      `/analyze` in Phase 3 per D3-01; any R6 follow-on) adds new ROWS to
      `sprk_analysisactions`, not new entities or prompt files. This task is the FIRST
      R5 instance of that pattern — get it right and the subsequent rows (D3-01 etc.)
      follow the template.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="Phase 1 (001-009)" status="not-started">
        Phase 1 ✅ gating per plan.md. While this task does not strictly require any
        Phase 1 code artifact to exist for the seed deploy ITSELF to succeed, the
        functional VALUE of the action row depends on the Phase 1 `FieldDelta`
        streaming pipeline (tasks 005 + 006) consuming the action's output schema. Per
        TASK-INDEX.md, Phase 1 must be ✅ before this task begins. Confirm at Step 1.
      </dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Insights Engine r2 `predict-matter-cost@v1` and `universal-ingest@v1`
        playbooks are the structural reference for the JPS action-row + playbook-row
        + node-rows triplet. The Insights INS-FACT / INS-IDXR / INS-EVID / INS-GRND /
        INS-DECL / INS-RART action rows are the JPS-format reference for the
        `sprk_systemprompt` shape.</item>
      <item>Task 011 (D2-02) deploys the `sprk_analysisplaybook` row + node row that
        references THIS task's action row via `actionCode = SUM-CHAT@v1`. The two
        tasks are parallel-safe per TASK-INDEX.md P2-G1 but the playbook deploy will
        skip-on-exists or recreate ONCE this action row exists, so if task 011 lands
        first the operator should re-run task 011's deploy after this task lands.</item>
      <item>Task 012 (D2-03) introduces the `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` that reads
        the action row at runtime via `AnalysisActionService.GetActionAsync` to load
        the `sprk_systemprompt`. The action's GUID is not used directly; lookup is by
        `sprk_actioncode`. This task does not need to know the GUID — Dataverse
        assigns it on insert.</item>
      <item>Task 040 (D3-01) `/analyze` configuration-only proof point will add a
        SECOND `sprk_analysisaction` seed using the same pattern this task establishes.
        Get the template right here.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL declaration">
      Check context usage. If &gt; 70%, create handoff summary and request `/compact`.
      Output the mandatory RIGOR LEVEL declaration per CLAUDE.md §8:

      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: Dataverse data deploy with BINDING idempotency + JPS prompt-shape
         contract that downstream tasks 011/012/014/015 + D3-01 depend on. R5 CLAUDE.md
         §10 BINDING gotcha applies (no new prompt-bearing entity). Establishes the
         R5 template for all future config-only action-row seeds.
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS TO EXECUTE: Steps 0-10 per task-execute SKILL.md Step 0.5.
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```

      Confirm `current-task.md` reflects task 010 active. Confirm no prior R5 task in
      flight.
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress + Dependencies">
      Read `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` and confirm: task 010 status is 🔲, wave P2-G1,
      parallel-safe = true, dependencies = "Phase 1 ✅". Confirm tasks 001 through 009
      are all ✅. If any Phase 1 task is still 🔲 / 🔄, STOP and report blocker per R5
      CLAUDE.md §6. Also confirm task 011 status (parallel-safe sibling); if it is
      ✅ already, the seed flow MUST still work (idempotency is bidirectional —
      `Deploy-Playbook.ps1` line 528-572 handles existing playbook).
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources + Verify Action-Row Convention on Spaarke Dev">
      Read EVERY file in &lt;inputs&gt; and &lt;knowledge&gt;. Specifically extract:
      (a) the existing `sprk_analysisaction` row shape — query Spaarke Dev for one of
      the INS-* rows via `az rest --method GET --url "$DATAVERSE_URL/api/data/v9.2/sprk_analysisactions?$filter=sprk_actioncode eq 'INS-FACT@v1'&$select=sprk_analysisactionid,sprk_name,sprk_actioncode,sprk_systemprompt,sprk_outputschemajson,sprk_configjson,_sprk_actiontypeid_value"` (or use `Resolve-ScopeCode` pattern from `Deploy-Playbook.ps1`); record which field carries the output schema (likely `sprk_outputschemajson` OR `sprk_configjson` embedding) — THIS IS THE BINDING SHAPE for the new row;
      (b) the `sprk_actiontype` lookup row appropriate for an LLM analysis node — use
      the same type used by the existing R-action Summarize row (likely `0 - AiAnalysis`
      per the convention in `predict-matter-cost@v1` line 11 `sprk_playbooktype: 0`);
      (c) confirm `SUM-CHAT@v1` does not collide with any existing `sprk_actioncode`
      by querying Spaarke Dev with `$filter=sprk_actioncode eq 'SUM-CHAT@v1'`.

      Record findings in `notes/task-010-action-shape-discovery.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Author JPS System Prompt">
      Author the `sprk_systemprompt` payload as a JPS-formatted string. Pattern:

      ```
      ROLE: You are the Spaarke Summarize-for-Chat assistant. You receive 1-N file
            chunks from a user's chat session and produce a structured summary.
      INPUT: file_chunks (array of { fileId, fileName, chunkText, chunkOrder })
      INSTRUCTIONS:
        - Emit a JSON object matching the output_schema EXACTLY.
        - Field emission order MUST be: tldr → summary → fileHighlights → mentionedParties → callToAction.
        - tldr: 3-5 concise bullets, ≤140 chars each. Emit FIRST.
        - summary: ≤2 paragraphs of prose. Emit SECOND.
        - fileHighlights: per-file highlight array (one entry per fileId in input).
        - mentionedParties: array of distinct parties named in the documents.
        - callToAction: ≤1 sentence suggesting the user's likely next step.
      DECLINE: If the input is insufficient to produce a faithful summary (no
               meaningful content, garbled extraction, sensitive-information block),
               return a declineResponse object per D-04 honesty contract instead of
               fabricating a summary. The orchestrator routes decline cases to
               DeclineToFindNode downstream.
      ```

      Inline the JPS XML/structured form (if existing Insights actions use XML
      stanzas) or the equivalent structured text form per the existing pattern
      surfaced at Step 2. DO NOT use a free-text prompt — use JPS exactly.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Author Output Schema (Structured-Outputs-Compatible JSON Schema)">
      Author the output schema (JSON Schema draft-07) covering the 5 top-level
      fields. Constraints: `additionalProperties: false`, required fields populated,
      no unsupported Structured-Outputs keywords (`anyOf`/`oneOf` only at the
      decline-discriminator if used). Field shape:

      ```json
      {
        "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
        "type": "object",
        "additionalProperties": false,
        "required": ["tldr", "summary", "fileHighlights", "mentionedParties", "callToAction"],
        "properties": {
          "tldr":            { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string", "maxLength": 140 }, "minItems": 3, "maxItems": 5 },
          "summary":         { "type": "string", "maxLength": 2000 },
          "fileHighlights":  { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "object", "additionalProperties": false, "required": ["fileId","fileName","highlights"], "properties": { "fileId": {"type":"string"}, "fileName": {"type":"string"}, "highlights": {"type":"array","items":{"type":"string"}} } } },
          "mentionedParties":{ "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } },
          "callToAction":    { "type": "string", "maxLength": 240 }
        }
      }
      ```

      Decide and record in task notes: does decline-to-find route through
      `DeclineToFindNode` (preferred per Insights pattern; schema above stays clean) or
      via a discriminated branch on the schema itself? Record the decision per spec
      FR-11 constraint.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Author Seed Deploy Artifact">
      Per the Step 2 decision on harness extension vs sibling script:
      Option A (PREFERRED — extends existing harness): Add an "actions" section to
      `scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1`'s definition-file schema so a playbook deploy can
      ALSO seed referenced actions in one pass. Author the new R5 definition file at
      `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Playbooks/summarize-for-chat.playbook.json`
      (mirror the existing Insights `Playbooks/` folder convention) with both an
      `actions` array (containing the SUM-CHAT@v1 seed) AND a `playbook` + `nodes`
      section that task 011 fills in. THIS TASK ships only the `actions` array; task
      011 ships the `playbook` + `nodes` sections in the SAME file.
      Option B (SIBLING SCRIPT): Author `scripts/Deploy-AnalysisAction.ps1` that
      reuses `Deploy-Playbook.ps1`'s `Get-DataverseHeaders` / `Invoke-DataversePost` /
      lookup-then-insert helpers. Action JSON lives at
      `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Playbooks/sum-chat-action.json`.
      Either option MUST be idempotent (lookup-then-insert by `sprk_actioncode`).
      Record the choice + rationale in task notes; preferred is Option A per R5 §3.1
      reuse mandate.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Dry-Run Deploy">
      Invoke the deploy harness in dry-run mode against Spaarke Dev:
      `pwsh scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1 -DefinitionFile <path> -DryRun` (Option A) or
      `pwsh scripts/Deploy-AnalysisAction.ps1 -DefinitionFile <path> -DryRun` (Option
      B). Confirm the dry-run output reports "WOULD CREATE action SUM-CHAT@v1" with
      the correct system prompt + output schema serialized. Capture output to task
      notes.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Live Deploy to Spaarke Dev (uses `dataverse-deploy` skill conventions)">
      Invoke the deploy harness against Spaarke Dev (use the `dataverse-deploy` skill
      per task-execute conventions — the skill handles `az login` verification +
      `DATAVERSE_URL` env-var resolution + PowerShell invocation pattern). Confirm
      the deploy reports "Created: &lt;guid&gt;" for the new action row. Capture stdout to
      `notes/task-010-deployment-evidence.md` including the new row's GUID.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify Action Row in Spaarke Dev">
      Issue a verification query against Spaarke Dev:
      `az rest --method GET --url "$DATAVERSE_URL/api/data/v9.2/sprk_analysisactions?$filter=sprk_actioncode eq 'SUM-CHAT@v1'&$select=sprk_analysisactionid,sprk_name,sprk_actioncode,sprk_systemprompt,sprk_outputschemajson,sprk_configjson,_sprk_actiontypeid_value"`.
      Confirm: (a) exactly one row returned; (b) `sprk_name` = "Summarize Document
      for Chat"; (c) `sprk_systemprompt` matches Step 3 output verbatim; (d) the
